<div>Get off your desk chair. Peel your eyes away from that computer screen. Cloth yourself in some smart shorts and a collared top and and join us in getting some fresh air in the beautiful scenery of a golf course!&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Golf is arguably the most sociable and relaxing game in existence. Unlike most sports, you can play golf whether you are 5 years old or 85 years old. Not to mention it being a highly popular corporate sport- for all of those future business men/women wishing to impress a client!</div><div>&nbsp;</div><p><strong>Are you an enthusiastic, single figured handicapper?</strong></p><div><strong>&nbsp;</strong></div><div><strong>Are you a casual golfer who loves to breeze the course with a few mates?</strong></div><div><strong>&nbsp;</strong></div><div><strong>Are you interested in learning to play golf?</strong></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>If the answer to any of these is YES, then the Golf Soc. is for you!<br /><div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;</div></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Butler's Golf Soc. is free to join and we are a very easy going society, aiming to get together 1-2 times a month to have a game of golf or hit the driving range up.&nbsp;Sadly the course next to Butler has closed, however it is only a short bus journey to the new course we play at, which is in great condition and offers a great student deal!</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Whether you own a set of golf clubs or not- get involved in Golf Soc.! If you have any further questions don't hesitate to get in contact with me (below). If not, I will see you at Butler's fresher's fair!</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><img src="http://www.bettergolfwithfitness.com/.a/6a00d8341e839953ef01156f3ac21c970c-800wi" alt="" /></div></div>